reviews.text: Top two so far across USA when it comes to GF pizza!!  Great service, thank you Michelle!  And, thank you, thoughtful owner/chef with one of the absolute best GF crusts ever!  Add a GF beer option and you couldn‚Äôt ask for more!!  We split the ‚ÄòGreen Salad‚Äô and an awesome GF ‚ÄòParma Pizza‚Äô and didn‚Äôt want the meal to end!  Thank you!

In town for work, this was recommended to me by the Chamber of Commerce. Insisted to try the meatballs, such a great suggestion, wasn't over done with the bread crumbs and tasted every bite of the meats and herbs, perfection. Then did half sausage and honey/spec & apricot, that spice from jalape√±os and the sweet from the apricot, personal choice add some blue cheese crumbs or more feta would have sent me over the top of heavenly goodness. Great recommendation. I want more!!!

The pizza was excellent and the service was really great. I guess it helped because we ate there somewhat after normal dinner hours.
But I would say the inside of the restaurant was entirely too smoky; it smelled really strong of mesquite wood smoke.
I don't know if it's the way they try to smoke their pizza or what, but we sat outside, which made it much more pleasant.

Ordered the Il Norcini, and the speck was VERY salty. We ended up picking it off, but the italian sausage and pepperoni were very good. Crust was wonderful and crunchy around the edges but soggy on the bottom. Had a small Caesar salad that was very good.

Pizza is so soft and out of this world. Beautiful vibe. Kind people.
Will be back. I got a half margarita and half jalape√±o sausage honey (per the other reviews and the recommendation from my Gal); I would recommend. Location is amazing. Near one of the best hotels (Holiday Inn express) and across the street from a good theater

detailedReviews.text: While dining in at Vicino Pizza in Riverstone, we were seated immediately out on the patio. The server was very helpful and attentive. Furthermore, why am I paying $1.00 for Hidden Valley Ranch!? This is an upscale Neapolitan pizza place‚Ä¶I‚Äôd expected more. The pizza itself was bland and appeared to be missing the peppers it said it came with. Truly disappointing.

This is a great pizza place located right across from the Regal Cinima, making the idea of pizza and a movie very plausible. I usually come after the movie with whomever I am watching with.
The pizza here is thin crust, not ultra thin but on the thin spectrum, and topped with the most amazing goodness. My favorite is the Spicy Cuppa. It‚Äôs covered in arugula, hiding all the delicious ingredients underneath.
Il Norcini is great for  meat lovers.
For a salad, the Vivino Chopped is an excellent and hardy salad.
They also have some great beer and cider on tap.
Service has always been top notch in a very clean environment. If you are by yourself or with one other person, it‚Äôs great to sit at bar and chat with the manager or server. They are good people to talk with.

I highly recommend eating here!

detailedReviews.text: We love coming to Vicino‚Äôs! The staff is always so welcoming and the food is always delicious! I am Gluten Free and they have a really good GF crust for the pizza. ( They do not have a dedicated GF oven, if cross contamination is an issue for you.) our favorites are the Spicy Coppa and the Sausage and Honey pizzas. Hubby loves the meatballs but they are not GF. They have an extensive wine list, I love their Green Salad (dried cherries! Yum!) and the Fritto Misto is one of our favorites, too. If you like your pizza Neapolitan style, you can‚Äôt go wrong here!

detailedReviews.author: Brandon O‚ÄôDonoghue
detailedReviews.text:
DO NOT EAT HERE
* If you like ranch with a side of pizza.
* If Pizza Hut is your gold standard.
* If you‚Äôre craving a 3,000-calorie grease bomb.

For everyone else: Vicino‚Äôs is the best pizza in Coeur d‚ÄôAlene‚Äîpossibly in the entire state. Honestly, it‚Äôs the best pizza I‚Äôve ever had.

I‚Äôve been coming here biweekly for three months, and every visit delivers the same results: incredible pizza, consistent quality, and friendly service.

Their red sauce pizzas are a masterclass in craft. The crust is blackened just right in their arch oven, offering structural integrity for a mighty bite while folding effortlessly into your hand like a taco. The ingredients? Always fresh. The meats? Delightfully unique. Forget pepperoni‚Äîthey use house made coppa speck, and it‚Äôs a game-changer.

The Spicy Coppa pizza: a perfect combination of heat, saltiness, and peppery arugula. The bitter greens balance the rich pork, all elevated by tangy olive oil on a crisp crust. It‚Äôs $20 well spent. Hesitant at first, I trusted the server‚Äôs recommendation, and she nailed it.

Feeling less adventurous? Try the Sausage & Honey pizza. I was skeptical too‚Äîhoney on pizza? After bad experiences at places like Mod, I avoided it. But here? It‚Äôs perfection. The fresh ingredients make all the difference, including the spicy jalape√±os that pack a punch.

Their meatballs? Next-level. Soft, tender, and bathed in a tomato sauce that feels like a bite of Italian heritage. Don‚Äôt skip them. The server informed me the recipe was over 100 years old and researched to infinity.

I heard the owner trained with Italian chefs who‚Äôve passed down generations of recipes. You can taste the refinement and authenticity in every bite. The photos in the restaurant are taken by the owner in Italy.

Service Matters‚Ä®The team at Vicino‚Äôs is cordial, attentive, and reassuring. I once mentioned needing everything spot-on for visiting friends after disappointing meals at ‚Äúpopular‚Äù spots (cold food, stale flavors, hair in the dishes). The server listened with genuine care and ensured everything came out perfect‚Äîand it did.

Try Vicino‚Äôs If You:
* Can‚Äôt risk a bad meal.
* Love authentic pizza.
* Appreciate great cuisine.
* Want to relax at a restaurant that cares.

Vicino‚Äôs isn‚Äôt just a pizza place‚Äîit‚Äôs a taste of heritage
